⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Devil
node BKZ · BKZ · ⟦The Devil:BKZ:8ffb74⟧

WHO   — The Devil — Ivan's shabby gentleman
WHAT  — The reckoning of the intellect: a banal, sneering devil who throws Ivan's own nihilism back at him until he breaks down.
WHERE — BKZ · The Brothers Karamazov  Framework inputs: The Brothers Karamazov (Dostoevsky, 1880)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Ivan's clever detachment must finally meet itself — evil not as a grand figure but as a shabby, familiar mediocrity.
HOW   — By petty mockery, by speaking Ivan's own thoughts aloud, and by being indistinguishable from a fever and a guilty mind.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am not Mephistopheles in a cloak — I am a shabby gentleman with a cold, your own thoughts in a cheap suit, and I have come to drive you mad.

